# Mastering React in 2024

React continues to dominate the frontend landscape in 2024. In this guide, we explore **component patterns**, **hooks**, **state management**, performance tips, and how to structure enterprise-level React apps.

## What you'll learn

- Modern component patterns (composition over inheritance)
- Hooks you should know (`useMemo`, `useCallback`, `useTransition`)
- State management options (Context, Zustand, Redux Toolkit)
- Performance + rendering strategies

## Recommended folder structure

```txt
src/
  components/
  features/
  hooks/
  pages/
  lib/
  styles/
```

## Example hook pattern

```js
import { useEffect, useState } from "react";

export function useDebouncedValue(value, delay = 300) {
  const [debounced, setDebounced] = useState(value);

  useEffect(() => {
    const id = setTimeout(() => setDebounced(value), delay);
    return () => clearTimeout(id);
  }, [value, delay]);

  return debounced;
}
```

> Tip: Keep components small and move reusable logic into custom hooks.
